fields.description:
The [JIRA issues macro with an applink server parameter|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Inserting+JIRA+Issues#InsertingJIRAIssues-shorthand] in Confluence does not currently work in Studio. Attempting to use it results in the following error on the rendered page:

{noformat}
jira: JQL and issue key arguments for this macro require at least one JIRA application link to be configured
{noformat}

A workaround is to add an Applinks 3 applink to JIRA in Confluence, but this requires system administrator priviledges.

When performing an import on Unicorn, it timed out while setting the FishEye repo permissions:

