I have several concerns with this:
* It shouldn't time out on a normal import.
* If it does time out, it shouldn't throw a 500 error and die horribly, it should handle the error responsibly.
* If an error is encountered, it shouldn't leave the import in a half-finished state, with some values imported correctly (e.g. issues) and some not (e.g. users).

