Studio instances apparently are not respecting _Default Access Levels_

If you set to No Access and create a user on Google Apps, the user is being created on JIRA Studio with Collaborator permissions.

Steps to reproduce:

# Have gapps already working on the instance;
# Disable the sync and change the _Default Level Access_ to _No Access_;
# Add new users on Gapps;
# Run a manual sync of your gapps integration or re-enable automatically sync from time to time;

The new users created will have Collaborators permissions and not be flagged as No Access

When viewing the build result, under the "Changes" tab, there is a URL pointing to the relevant code change viewable in FishEye. The URL seems to be wrong. For example, it points to something like below in my test environment:
